title: fanoutqa: What is the student population of the 5 oldest universities in the world? (59f805bb72e71948)

chat_history.content: What is the student population of the 5 oldest universities in the world?

The 5 oldest universities in the world are:

1. University of Al-Qarawiyyin (859)
2. University of Bologna (1088)
3. University of Oxford (1096)
4. University of Salamanca (1134)
5. University of Paris (1150)

As of 2023, data for the student population of these universities is not readily available. However, here are the student populations of these universities from the latest date I could find:

| University | Student Population |
|---|---|
| University of Al-Qarawiyyin | 15,000 (2015) |
| University of Bologna | 80,000 (2021) |
| University of Oxford | 24,080 (2022) |
| University of Salamanca | 30,662 (2014) |
| University of Paris | N/A |

Please note that sources differ on the number of students at the University of Al-Qarawiyyin, with some stating that the university has 15,000 students and others stating that it has 5,000 students.

You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.
